    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "You can fix the worst of the issue by using font.Measure to measure the text and then relayout the dialog to set the correct margins on all 4 sides.  If the text is smaller than the minimum (defined by the dialog yaml layout) it should be centered within the dialog, otherwise the dialog should be expanded to make it fit.\n\nWe do exactly this for at least one tooltip type, but I don't know off the top of my head which it is.\n\nYou can also use the WidgetUtils.TruncateText helper to reduce the length of the file path to something reasonably printable.\n"
  },
